00:25.470 --> 00:27.220
You all right?

00:27.390 --> 00:28.810
Shit's really hitting the fan.

00:28.970 --> 00:30.890
<i>What difference does it make?</i>

00:31.060 --> 00:33.270
<i>- That's a different study.
But if we knew that-</i>

00:33.440 --> 00:36.020
<i>We don't know that.
We don't know that.</i>

00:36.190 --> 00:38.190
<i>We've gotta operate
on what we do know.</i>

00:38.360 --> 00:39.940
I'm still dreaming.

00:40.110 --> 00:41.490
No, you're not.

00:41.650 --> 00:45.070
<i>It's human beings
whose lives we're trying to save.</i>

00:45.700 --> 00:46.780
My turn with the coat.

00:46.950 --> 00:48.870
<i>I try to explain several times.</i>

00:49.040 --> 00:51.000
The guys on the crew are going crazy.

00:51.160 --> 00:53.790
A couple of them
have flown the coop already.

00:54.960 --> 00:56.880
I don't know how long
we're gonna stay on the air.

01:02.130 --> 01:03.720
Who's on camera?
Who the hell's on camera?

01:03.880 --> 01:05.840
Who the hell's on camera two,
a blind man?

01:08.510 --> 01:10.970
Roll the rescue-
Roll the rescue stations.

01:11.140 --> 01:14.230
We just got a report that half those
stations have been knocked out.

01:14.390 --> 01:15.400
Get me another list.

01:15.560 --> 01:18.190
Sure, I'll just pull it out of my ass, right?

01:18.360 --> 01:20.360
<i>- Believe the dead are returning to life?
- I'm not...</i>

01:20.530 --> 01:23.190
You believe the dead are returning
to life and attacking the living?

01:23.360 --> 01:25.030
I'm not so sure what to believe, doctor.

01:25.200 --> 01:27.870
All we get is what you people tell us,
it's hard enough to believe...

01:28.030 --> 01:29.030
It's fact. It's fact.

01:29.200 --> 01:31.370
It's hard enough to believe
without you coming in here-

01:31.540 --> 01:34.120
You're not running a talk show here,
Mr. Berman.

01:34.290 --> 01:37.750
You can forget pitching an audience
the moral bullshit they wanna hear.

01:37.920 --> 01:40.380
<i>You're talking about
abandoning human...</i>

01:44.720 --> 01:48.220
Frannie, get the list of rescue stations.
Charlie's receiving on the emergencies.

01:48.390 --> 01:50.220
Rescue stations?

01:50.390 --> 01:52.270
Half of those are inoperative as of now.

01:52.430 --> 01:53.890
Charlie, these are rescue stations.

01:54.060 --> 01:56.270
We can't send people
in inoperative rescue stations.

01:56.440 --> 01:59.400
We've had old information on the air
for the last 12 hours.

02:13.290 --> 02:14.910
- Kill those old ones.
- Givens wants them.

02:15.080 --> 02:18.120
Kill them, Dick. Tell Givens to see me.

02:22.960 --> 02:24.170
You have not listened.

02:24.340 --> 02:27.590
You have not listened in the situation
for three weeks.

02:27.760 --> 02:29.010
What does it take?

02:29.180 --> 02:31.220
What does it take to make people see?

02:31.390 --> 02:33.520
People aren't willing to accept
your solutions, doctor.

02:33.680 --> 02:35.060
And I, for one, don't blame them.

02:35.230 --> 02:40.440
Every dead body that is not exterminated
becomes one of them.

02:40.610 --> 02:42.440
Il gets up and kills.

02:42.610 --> 02:45.280
The people it kills get up and kill.

02:45.440 --> 02:48.200
Operative rescue stations.

02:49.280 --> 02:51.070
Dan!

02:55.120 --> 02:57.460
Yeah, that's the one, kid. Type that up.

02:58.920 --> 03:01.630
They're dropping like flies.
I think Foster's right. We're losing it.

03:01.790 --> 03:03.170
We're blowing it ourselves.

03:03.340 --> 03:05.210
What's going on?
Who killed those supers?

03:05.380 --> 03:07.630
I didn't order to do that.

03:07.800 --> 03:09.880
Garrett, who told you
to kill those supers?

03:10.050 --> 03:12.220
Nobody, I killed them.
They're out of date.

03:12.390 --> 03:14.350
- Do you know you're on the air?
- What is going on?

03:14.510 --> 03:16.930
I want those supers on the air
all the time.

03:17.100 --> 03:21.060
Without those rescue situations on-screen
every minute, people won't watch us.

03:21.230 --> 03:22.310
They'll tune out.

03:22.480 --> 03:24.900
You willing to murder people
by sending them to stations...

03:25.070 --> 03:26.110
...that have closed down?

03:26.280 --> 03:29.320
I want that list up on the screen
every minute that we're on the air.

03:29.490 --> 03:31.820
Anybody need a ride?
- What the hell are you doing?

03:31.990 --> 03:33.240
Get back here on this console.

03:33.410 --> 03:35.580
What is this, the news show
or a football game?

03:35.740 --> 03:37.750
Get that idiot off the air!

03:37.910 --> 03:40.830
This is supposed to be a doggone
news television show!

03:41.000 --> 03:42.710
Officer, stop those men.

03:42.880 --> 03:45.500
Lucas, get back here on the console!

03:45.670 --> 03:47.420
Damn.

03:48.380 --> 03:50.380
Get somebody in here
who can run this thing.

03:50.550 --> 03:52.180
Get that fucking idiot off the air!

03:52.340 --> 03:54.680
Get someone. Triple pay!

03:54.850 --> 03:56.720
We're staying on the air!

03:56.890 --> 03:59.270
My God. Turn it off!

03:59.430 --> 04:02.190
Dr. Foster, so what's the facts?
The public needs facts.

04:02.350 --> 04:03.480
What do you have to give us?

04:03.650 --> 04:06.820
They kill for one reason.
They kill for food.

04:06.980 --> 04:09.280
They eat their victims.
Do you understand that, Mr. Berman?

04:09.440 --> 04:10.860
That's what keeps them going.

04:12.200 --> 04:15.370
If we'd listened, if we'd dealt
with this phenomenon properly...

04:15.530 --> 04:20.829
...without emotion, without emotion,
it wouldn't have come to this.

04:21.500 --> 04:24.710
There is a martial law state
in effect in Philadelphia...

04:24.880 --> 04:28.590
...as in all other major cities
in the country,

04:28.760 --> 04:32.050
Hold it, friend. Need a badge.

04:32.220 --> 04:33.220
Hey, what's going on?

04:33.380 --> 04:34.550
It's just crazy.

04:40.680 --> 04:42.100
Here.

04:42.810 --> 04:43.810
Jim, you take it.

04:43.980 --> 04:48.400
It is the order of the OEP by command
of the federal government...

04:48.570 --> 04:50.570
...the president of the United States.

04:51.440 --> 04:54.910
Citizens may no longer occupy
private residences...

04:55.070 --> 04:57.990
...no matter how safely protected
or well-stocked.

04:58.830 --> 05:03.370
The dead body must be exterminated
either by destroying the brain...

05:03.540 --> 05:05.830
...or severing the brain
from the rest of the body.

05:06.500 --> 05:08.210
Should we be unable to change...

05:08.380 --> 05:10.760
Frannie, meet me on the roof at 9:00.
We're getting out.

05:10.920 --> 05:13.130
- I don't believe this, what...?
- Get out in the chopper.

05:13.300 --> 05:14.930
David, we can't, we've got...

05:17.550 --> 05:18.550
Is 9 p. m. all right?

05:18.720 --> 05:21.640
- Stephen, we can't. We've got to-
- We've got to nothing, Fran.

05:21.810 --> 05:24.060
We've got to survive.
Somebody's got to survive.

05:24.230 --> 05:28.020
Now, you be upstairs at 9:00,
and don't make me come looking for you.

05:28.190 --> 05:30.190
Go ahead. We'll be off the air
by midnight anyway.

05:30.360 --> 05:33.280
The emergency networks
are taking over.

05:34.320 --> 05:36.530
Our responsibility is finished.

05:36.700 --> 05:39.450
Moved in the central areas of the city.

05:39.620 --> 05:43.080
The bodies of the dead
will be delivered over...

05:43.250 --> 05:45.830
...to specially equipped squads
of the national guard...

05:46.620 --> 05:48.540
Martinez.

05:48.710 --> 05:51.880
You know we've got this building
surrounded.

05:52.630 --> 05:56.300
Little bastard's got them moved
into one building. Dumb little bastard.

05:56.720 --> 05:59.010
- Come on.
Martinez.

05:59.470 --> 06:02.470
The people in this project
are your responsibility.

06:03.060 --> 06:04.810
We don't want any of them hurt.

06:04.980 --> 06:08.770
There were no charges
against you or any of your people.

06:08.940 --> 06:10.610
Yet.

06:11.610 --> 06:12.980
Come on, Martinez,

06:13.150 --> 06:15.490
Yeah, Martinez,
show your greasy little Puerto Rican ass...

06:15.650 --> 06:16.900
...so I can blow it right off.

06:18.070 --> 06:20.740
Blow all their asses off,
lowlife bastards.

06:20.910 --> 06:25.580
Blow all their lowlife little Puerto Rican
and nigger asses right off,

06:26.330 --> 06:27.830
- You're Rod, right?
- Rod Tucker.

06:28.000 --> 06:30.040
How the hell come we stick
these lowlife bastards...

06:30.210 --> 06:32.210
...in these big ass fancy hotels anyway?

06:32.380 --> 06:34.630
Shit, man. This is better than I got.

06:34.800 --> 06:36.590
Hey, you ain't gonna talk them
out of here.

06:36.760 --> 06:39.140
- You gotta blow them out.
- Just stay cool, okay?

06:39.300 --> 06:41.260
When we go in there, don't pop off,
all right?

06:41.430 --> 06:42.430
I'll be okay.

06:42.600 --> 06:45.480
Come on, let's get on with it.
This is a waste of my time.

06:46.310 --> 06:48.020
Let's go, let's go!

06:49.850 --> 06:50.860
Jesus Christ.

06:52.520 --> 06:54.530
Move in. Move in.

06:54.690 --> 06:55.690
Goddamn it.

06:57.530 --> 06:59.660
Come on, you dumb bastards.
Come and get them.

07:16.710 --> 07:18.050
Rico, look out!

07:30.060 --> 07:31.650
Hold it.

07:35.780 --> 07:37.570
Don't go out there!

07:41.240 --> 07:42.490
<i>Gas. Gas.</i>

07:42.660 --> 07:44.160
Masks.

07:44.330 --> 07:47.120
Masks for gas. Masks for gas.
Down there.

07:47.290 --> 07:50.080
Come on, work yourselves down.
One floor at a time. Deep down here.

07:53.170 --> 07:55.420
- Hands up.
- Damn.

08:01.590 --> 08:03.470
Steve, don't go!

08:03.640 --> 08:05.260
No, let me go!

08:07.600 --> 08:10.810
Come on, you little bastards, ha, ha.

08:17.980 --> 08:20.110
Wooley's gone ape shit, man.

08:20.950 --> 08:22.950
- Woo ley!
- He-he-he-hey.

08:26.830 --> 08:29.450
Give me a hand here, man.

08:31.790 --> 08:32.789
Yah!

08:32.960 --> 08:34.789
What the hell, man?! Leave me alone!

08:34.960 --> 08:36.210
Give me a hand, somebody!

08:36.710 --> 08:37.960
Don't do anything, man.

08:39.340 --> 08:41.970
Goddamn it. Help me, he's crazy.

08:42.130 --> 08:43.179
Step away from him.

08:45.680 --> 08:47.140
Not that room. Not that room.

09:19.050 --> 09:20.670
Do that again.

09:20.840 --> 09:22.340
Come on.

09:27.430 --> 09:28.550
Jesus Christ.

09:30.510 --> 09:32.680
Come on, come on,
You don't want to see that.

09:36.850 --> 09:38.020
Shoot it, man.

09:40.520 --> 09:43.440
Shoot it, man.
Shoot it in the head.

10:34.250 --> 10:35.290
<b>No! No!</b>

10:35.910 --> 10:36.910
Miguel.

10:38.420 --> 10:41.500
Miguel. Miguelito.

10:46.090 --> 10:47.430
Watch out for the girl.

10:47.590 --> 10:48.970
For chrissakes, stand clear.

10:58.390 --> 11:02.440
Oh, no, please. No, no, please.

11:15.290 --> 11:18.960
You ain't just in here
by yourself, boy.

11:25.920 --> 11:27.550
You was in Wooley's unit, wasn't you?

11:29.800 --> 11:31.800
I didn't see nothing.

11:32.800 --> 11:33.970
I didn't see how he died.

12:10.670 --> 12:13.590
Mao, there's a lot of people
who were running out.

12:15.100 --> 12:16.810
I could run.

12:21.390 --> 12:24.060
I could run right tonight.

12:32.780 --> 12:35.120
Friend of mine's got this helicopter.

12:36.370 --> 12:38.410
He asked me to come with him.

12:39.540 --> 12:40.540
Think it's right to run?

12:51.010 --> 12:54.220
Setters, please let me pass.

12:55.300 --> 12:57.720
Let's get him to the medics.

12:57.890 --> 13:00.220
No, no, please.

13:00.850 --> 13:02.350
Just let me pass.

13:02.520 --> 13:05.440
I go up to seventh floor to find my sister.

13:05.600 --> 13:07.570
Just let me pass.

13:07.730 --> 13:10.110
The people of 107 will do
what you wish now.

13:16.570 --> 13:21.000
Many have died last week
on these streets.

13:21.410 --> 13:24.460
In the basement of this building,
you'll find them.

13:25.250 --> 13:27.840
I have given them the last rites.

13:28.000 --> 13:31.170
Now, you do what you will.

13:31.340 --> 13:34.430
You are stronger than us.

13:34.590 --> 13:38.800
But soon, I think they be stronger
than you.

13:43.640 --> 13:49.730
When the dead walk, senores,
we must stop the killing...

13:49.900 --> 13:52.280
...or we lose the war,

14:25.980 --> 14:29.480
Hurry, get up! Get it off!

15:47.310 --> 15:48.430
Jesus Christ.

15:50.140 --> 15:51.900
Hey, you okay down there?

15:52.060 --> 15:53.230
Yeah.

15:54.020 --> 15:56.070
This must be
where they dumped them in, huh?

15:57.070 --> 15:59.900
- You need more men?
- No, it's all done, man.

16:00.070 --> 16:02.070
It's all been done.

16:02.240 --> 16:04.830
Jesus Christ.

16:14.250 --> 16:16.250
Why did these people keep them here?

16:16.630 --> 16:20.590
Because they still believe
there's respect in dying.

16:25.930 --> 16:27.930
<i>...captain.</i>

16:29.930 --> 16:31.810
<i>Moving on the top fl...</i>

16:32.690 --> 16:34.440
<i>The line's not coming in at all.</i>

16:34.610 --> 16:37.730
Hello, HQ, this is police dock.

16:38.280 --> 16:41.990
Operator dead. Post abandoned.

16:44.780 --> 16:46.120
Stephen.

16:48.200 --> 16:49.240
I hope that's Roger.

16:58.710 --> 17:00.460
You guys okay?

17:00.630 --> 17:01.630
Who's he?

17:01.800 --> 17:03.130
His name is Peter. He's all right.

17:03.300 --> 17:04.510
Come on, let's hustle.

17:06.680 --> 17:09.140
Hey, you guys,
you better get a move on.

17:09.310 --> 17:11.180
There's a report at the dock's
being knocked out.

17:11.349 --> 17:12.890
Right. The left squad.

17:13.060 --> 17:14.520
Can we carry the extra weight?

17:14.690 --> 17:17.060
A little harder on the fuel,
but we'll be okay.

17:19.440 --> 17:21.319
Hey, you got any cigarettes?

17:22.859 --> 17:24.150
Any of you guys got cigarettes?

17:26.160 --> 17:27.410
No, sorry.

17:27.569 --> 17:28.780
Where you headed?

17:28.950 --> 17:30.160
Downriver.

17:30.330 --> 17:32.500
We got an idea.
Maybe we can make it to the islands.

17:32.910 --> 17:34.790
What islands?

17:34.960 --> 17:36.630
Any island.

17:36.790 --> 17:38.710
What about you? Where you headed?

17:38.880 --> 17:40.170
Straight up.

17:50.180 --> 17:51.270
Have you got any cigarettes?

17:52.680 --> 17:56.400
I never had a cigarette.
Did any of you guys got cigarettes?

18:22.090 --> 18:23.260
Is he your man?

18:24.720 --> 18:25.800
Most of the time, yeah.

18:28.590 --> 18:31.010
Just like to know who everybody is.

18:31.180 --> 18:32.470
Yeah, me too.

18:45.320 --> 18:47.240
Got any more water?

18:53.080 --> 18:54.160
You know where we are?

18:54.910 --> 18:56.580
Yeah, I know exactly where we are.

18:56.750 --> 18:58.040
Harrisburg?

18:58.210 --> 18:59.330
Passed it about an hour ago.

19:06.800 --> 19:10.220
Jesus. It's everywhere.

19:11.720 --> 19:14.140
We're still pretty close to Johnstown.

19:14.310 --> 19:16.480
Those rednecks are probably enjoying
the whole thing.

19:23.610 --> 19:24.610
What are you looking at?

19:24.940 --> 19:26.110
Happy hunting.

19:29.950 --> 19:32.780
I heard there about
ten or 12 down in the woods.

19:34.620 --> 19:38.620
I got at least 14 shells...

19:38.790 --> 19:41.460
I got a couple extra boxes
in case they come around later on.

20:14.950 --> 20:16.290
Look out, behind you.

20:16.450 --> 20:18.160
Get down, get down. Get out of the way!

20:21.670 --> 20:22.670
There, by the old car.

20:25.000 --> 20:26.670
Hit the gas tank.

20:38.430 --> 20:39.430
Shit.

20:39.600 --> 20:40.850
<b>Ah.</b>

20:41.020 --> 20:43.020
Eh, got him.

20:43.690 --> 20:45.400
Ah, missed.

20:49.070 --> 20:50.110
Got the bitch.

21:17.430 --> 21:20.270
Ah, shit, man, damn near empty.

21:20.430 --> 21:22.180
I got this one.

21:22.730 --> 21:25.900
There's a lot of private planes
in farm country like this.

21:26.060 --> 21:27.940
I guess they all hit the pumps
and they took off,

21:28.110 --> 21:29.320
Yeah, to where?

21:29.480 --> 21:30.730
I got some here.

21:31.150 --> 21:33.200
- Can you handle that?
- Yeah, I got it.

21:34.740 --> 21:37.240
I'm gonna see what's left
in the hangars.

22:29.500 --> 22:30.960
Bunch of junk.

22:48.150 --> 22:49.860
Stephen?

23:01.410 --> 23:04.450
Run! Run!

23:05.580 --> 23:06.660
Run!

23:07.870 --> 23:09.500
Run!

23:09.790 --> 23:10.790
<b>Oh.</b>

23:33.820 --> 23:35.610
Run.

23:51.630 --> 23:52.630
Roger!

25:27.890 --> 25:30.680
It's all right. It's okay. It's all right.

25:30.850 --> 25:32.520
Peter!

25:33.140 --> 25:35.520
Son of a bitch.

25:52.790 --> 25:55.830
You never aim a gun at anyone, mister.

25:57.080 --> 25:58.380
Peter!

25:58.540 --> 26:01.500
Scary, isn't it?

26:06.180 --> 26:07.640
Isn't it?

26:13.890 --> 26:16.850
We gotta find fuel.
Maybe closer to Cleveland.

26:17.020 --> 26:18.900
No, we gotta stay out of the big cities.

26:19.060 --> 26:21.070
If it's like Philly,
we may never get out alive.

26:21.230 --> 26:23.190
We may never get out
of any place alive.

26:23.360 --> 26:24.780
We almost didn't get out of here.

26:24.950 --> 26:26.570
We're getting out of here fine.

26:26.740 --> 26:29.240
As long as there's not many
of those around, we can handle them.

26:29.410 --> 26:32.450
Yeah, well, it wasn't those things
that nearly blew me away.

26:32.620 --> 26:34.540
We gotta stay in the sticks.

26:36.040 --> 26:38.330
I mean, there's bound to be more
private airports upstate.

26:38.500 --> 26:41.880
There's the locks along the Allegheny.
Fuel stations there, state, private.

26:42.050 --> 26:44.710
Those are probably still manned.
We don't need those hassles either.

26:44.880 --> 26:48.390
- They're just out after scavengers, looters.
- You got papers for this limousine?

26:48.550 --> 26:50.220
I got GON ID. So does Fran.

26:50.390 --> 26:52.890
Right, and we're out
doing traffic reports.

26:53.060 --> 26:54.350
Wake up, sucker.

26:54.520 --> 26:57.640
We're thieves and we're bad guys.
That's exactly what we are.

26:58.480 --> 27:00.400
We gotta find our own way.

27:00.560 --> 27:02.020
We don't even know
where we're going.

27:02.190 --> 27:05.820
We don't have food, we don't have water.
We don't even have a radio.

27:06.700 --> 27:09.570
Stephen, you need to get some sleep.

27:20.420 --> 27:22.040
What the hell is it?

27:22.210 --> 27:27.010
Looks like a shopping center,
one of those big indoor malls.

28:06.300 --> 28:07.300
Oh, my God.

28:07.460 --> 28:08.760
No chance. Let's get out of here.

28:08.920 --> 28:11.720
- Wait a minute. They can't get up here.
We can't go down there.

28:11.890 --> 28:13.970
Let's check it out.

28:37.910 --> 28:41.000
Most of the gates are down.
I don't think they can get into the stores.

28:41.160 --> 28:43.460
I haven't seen any of them
up on the second floor.

28:43.630 --> 28:46.000
The big department stores
usually use both floors.

28:46.170 --> 28:47.500
If we can get in up top...

28:48.050 --> 28:49.760
Okay.

29:04.400 --> 29:07.440
Guess the power's not off in this area.
Could be nuclear.

29:07.820 --> 29:10.030
What are they doing?
Why do they come here?

29:10.190 --> 29:11.280
Some kind of instinct.

29:12.030 --> 29:15.240
Memory of what they used to do.

29:15.410 --> 29:17.410
This was an important place
in their lives.

29:18.870 --> 29:21.700
Hey, look at this.

29:24.710 --> 29:27.040
This doesn't go down into the mall.

29:27.210 --> 29:28.880
What the hell is this?

29:35.930 --> 29:37.970
How do we get down there?

30:16.630 --> 30:18.090
Come down. Come on, drop.

30:19.350 --> 30:21.100
There, let's go.

30:23.270 --> 30:25.270
Looks like a free lunch.

30:27.600 --> 30:28.810
"SPAM."

