35:15.890 --> 35:17.390
You got it.

35:29.030 --> 35:32.780
Jesus Christ. They're maniacs.

35:33.780 --> 35:34.830
Wait.

35:49.630 --> 35:51.090
All right.

35:53.140 --> 35:55.180
Come on.

35:57.810 --> 35:59.270
Stephen, don't go down there.

35:59.440 --> 36:00.600
Why? What's the matter?

36:00.770 --> 36:02.610
Won't open.

36:03.440 --> 36:04.440
Not working.

36:06.530 --> 36:08.440
- To the right.
- Let's go.

36:23.960 --> 36:25.090
Come on.

36:28.460 --> 36:30.130
Come on, don't give in.

36:34.010 --> 36:35.970
Don't open the door, Come on, let up.

36:43.940 --> 36:45.860
Let it go, Take care of the other one.

36:53.570 --> 36:55.830
Stephen, for God's sake.

36:55.990 --> 36:57.990
Let's get up to the roof.

36:58.160 --> 37:00.540
We can't leave those guys down there.

37:00.710 --> 37:03.620
Well, we're in. Now how the hell
are we gonna get back?!

37:03.790 --> 37:05.880
Who the hell cares?
Let's go shopping first!

37:07.420 --> 37:08.420
Whoo!
Ah!

37:08.590 --> 37:09.630
Watches. Watches.

37:09.800 --> 37:11.800
Hey, hey, hey,
let's get the stuff we need.

37:11.970 --> 37:13.340
I'll get a television and a radio.

37:13.510 --> 37:16.600
Oh, lighter fluid,
and chocolates, chocolates.

37:16.760 --> 37:17.760
Okay.

37:19.470 --> 37:21.180
Whoo!
Oh, I'm gonna need a coat.

37:21.350 --> 37:24.150
Why not? It's about time.
Whoo!

37:46.580 --> 37:49.250
Hey, man, we can't carry all that shit.

37:50.550 --> 37:52.720
Oh, I see, we're gonna just wheel
right by them.

37:52.880 --> 37:53.970
We gonna try, brother.

37:54.130 --> 37:57.220
We ain't doing this for the exercise.
We might as well try to get what we can.

37:57.390 --> 37:59.810
No way this is gonna happen.

38:19.280 --> 38:20.990
Hey, Peter!

38:21.160 --> 38:25.370
Whoa! Whoo-hoo! Yeah!

38:30.750 --> 38:33.630
All right, let's go, brother.
The old okeydoke.

38:33.800 --> 38:35.470
- Okay.
- All right.

38:36.840 --> 38:38.430
Hey, hey, ugly.

38:38.590 --> 38:40.260
Let's raise some hell. Hey, hey.

38:40.930 --> 38:42.720
- Come here, chump. Come here.
- Come on.

38:42.890 --> 38:43.930
Hey, hey.

38:44.100 --> 38:45.270
Hey, come on!

38:45.430 --> 38:47.270
- Come on over here.
- Over here, that's right.

38:47.440 --> 38:50.230
Come on, come on, come on.

38:50.900 --> 38:51.900
Come here.

38:52.070 --> 38:55.030
Come on.
Come here. Whoo, whoo, whoo.

38:55.190 --> 38:57.410
- All right, come on.
- Hey, hey, hey.

38:57.570 --> 38:59.490
Come on, over here.

39:01.950 --> 39:05.580
Just give it time. Give it time.

39:27.020 --> 39:29.480
Okay, they're coming.

39:29.650 --> 39:32.310
Go on up. Stay out of sight.

39:32.480 --> 39:33.860
Let me know when it's clear enough.

39:34.020 --> 39:35.990
- Okay.
- Okay.

39:37.400 --> 39:41.870
Come to papa. That's it, keep coming.
Keep coming.

39:42.030 --> 39:44.790
Good, good, good.

39:50.670 --> 39:53.500
- Peter, it's good. Let's do it.
- Is it clear?

39:53.670 --> 39:55.500
Not altogether,
but they're spread out good.

39:55.920 --> 39:57.340
I think we can move the wagon.

39:57.510 --> 39:59.840
<i>I'm coming.</i>

40:33.580 --> 40:34.590
What the hell is that?

40:34.750 --> 40:35.880
I don't know. Fuzz maybe?

40:36.050 --> 40:38.590
- Maybe flyboy. Where's it coming from?
- Don't know. I can't tell.

41:31.270 --> 41:32.520
Come on. Open up.

41:32.690 --> 41:35.270
- Maybe I ought to go with you.
- Open up, I can get the wagon over.

41:35.440 --> 41:37.440
If it's flyboy, let's get him on our side.

41:37.610 --> 41:38.820
Okay.

41:42.240 --> 41:43.360
Just cover me good, you hear?

41:43.530 --> 41:45.280
You got it.

42:58.810 --> 43:00.440
Hold it, flyboy.

43:00.610 --> 43:02.110
Don't go into the stairway.

43:04.530 --> 43:07.200
Don't open that door, baby.
You'll lead them right up with you.

43:08.410 --> 43:09.870
Run for it. Run this way.

43:14.370 --> 43:17.370
That's it, come on. Run, run, run.

43:17.540 --> 43:20.830
Come on. All right, all right, all right.

43:21.790 --> 43:25.550
Now head for the department store. Go.

43:43.570 --> 43:45.400
Come on, come on,

43:48.990 --> 43:51.410
Okay, downstairs again, same trick.
Let's go.

45:09.940 --> 45:12.650
What do we do?
- Let them know we're here.

45:15.660 --> 45:17.240
Come on, let's go. Over here.

45:18.660 --> 45:21.120
You did all right this time, flyboy.
How about it?

45:24.420 --> 45:25.420
Over here.

45:27.630 --> 45:28.630
Come on.

45:42.430 --> 45:45.400
<i>Now this is time to save shoppers...</i>

45:45.560 --> 45:47.520
<i>...with our weekend sale-o-rama.</i>

45:48.360 --> 45:51.690
<i>Chairs sold with sectional love seats
all reduced.</i>

45:52.570 --> 45:55.700
<i>- This week's major offer...
- Jesus Christ.</i>

45:55.860 --> 46:00.240
<i>...is a contemporary dining room set
with a 40-by-60 burlap tablecloth...</i>

46:06.330 --> 46:10.710
<i>Why pay more
when the sales are often right here?</i>

46:10.880 --> 46:13.970
- We'll have a hell of a time getting back.
- We gotta wait before we move.

46:14.130 --> 46:16.890
No. There's always a chance of some
of them staying up on the balcony.

46:17.050 --> 46:18.800
We can handle that. Break through them.

46:18.970 --> 46:21.890
If any of them see us or hear us,
they'll just follow us on up.

46:22.060 --> 46:23.060
It's no good.

46:23.230 --> 46:27.230
We sure in hell can outrun them. Load up
what we got and get the hell out of here.

46:27.900 --> 46:29.520
I've been thinking...

46:29.690 --> 46:31.730
...maybe we got
a good thing going here.

46:31.900 --> 46:33.740
Maybe we shouldn't be
in such a hurry to leave.

46:33.900 --> 46:34.990
Oh, man.

46:35.150 --> 46:37.780
If we can get back up there,
without them catching on...

46:37.950 --> 46:39.490
...we can hold up for a while.

46:39.660 --> 46:41.540
At least long enough to catch a breath.

46:41.700 --> 46:43.540
Check out the radio.
See what's happening.

46:44.410 --> 46:47.580
There's some kind of passageway
over the tops of these stores.

46:48.250 --> 46:51.590
I don't know if it's just heating ducts
or some kind of access.

46:52.500 --> 46:54.550
I saw it on a map.

46:56.340 --> 46:58.510
Upstairs. Let's go.

47:07.770 --> 47:09.730
These are just lighting fixtures.

47:09.900 --> 47:12.770
No, it's got to be in this area.
It's on the map.

47:12.940 --> 47:14.650
Elevator shaft.

47:22.330 --> 47:24.290
Hold the doors.

47:33.300 --> 47:34.300
It's here.

47:34.460 --> 47:37.010
Get me a screwdriver and something
to stand on from down there.

47:37.170 --> 47:40.390
<b>Uh, I know where the tools are.
Why don't you grab that stool over there?</b>

47:48.980 --> 47:51.400
It's all right. We can get it off.

47:51.560 --> 47:52.650
You found it, fly boy.

47:56.990 --> 48:00.160
One-stop shopping. Everything you need
right at your fingertips.

48:00.320 --> 48:02.030
Phillips.
- Here you go,

48:16.840 --> 48:17.840
Stephen?

48:39.700 --> 48:41.700
Sweet Jesus.

48:41.860 --> 48:43.740
I've seen it. Come on.

50:44.530 --> 50:47.160
Don't shoot.
They'll hear you downstairs.

51:24.230 --> 51:25.740
Looks like we're gonna be okay.

51:32.370 --> 51:36.080
You should see all the great stuff we got,
Frannie. All kinds of stuff.

51:36.250 --> 51:38.330
This place is terrific.

51:38.500 --> 51:40.790
It really is. It's perfect.

51:40.960 --> 51:43.040
All kinds of things.

51:43.210 --> 51:46.050
We really got it made here, Frannie.

51:59.560 --> 52:01.060
What the hell time is it, anyway?

52:01.230 --> 52:02.400
Not quite 9.

52:02.560 --> 52:03.570
And nothing?

52:03.730 --> 52:07.440
As long as we're getting the pattern,
that must mean they're sending the signal.

52:18.500 --> 52:23.460
<i>No longer
seek occupancy in private residences...</i>

52:23.630 --> 52:27.760
<i>...no matter how safe
or well-protected they may be.</i>

52:29.590 --> 52:32.090
<i>The president today
has sent to Congress...</i>

52:32.260 --> 52:33.930
<i>...a package of initiatives...</i>

52:34.100 --> 52:37.270
<i>...aimed at what sources call
a most sweeping set...</i>

52:37.430 --> 52:39.640
She all right? She looks blown.

52:39.810 --> 52:42.980
- What do you expect?
- No, I mean she really looks sick.

52:43.150 --> 52:44.940
- Physically.
- She's pregnant.

52:45.570 --> 52:47.570
<i>That communications with Detroit...</i>

52:47.730 --> 52:48.780
<i>...have been knocked out...</i>

52:50.650 --> 52:52.410
<i>...along with Atlanta, Boston...</i>

52:52.570 --> 52:53.620
Well, how far along?

52:53.780 --> 52:55.120
Three and a half, four months.

52:55.280 --> 52:56.280
Jesus.

52:57.740 --> 52:59.290
Maybe we should try to get moving.

52:59.450 --> 53:00.460
We can deal with it.

53:00.620 --> 53:02.460
Yeah, but maybe she needs
a doctor or something.

53:02.620 --> 53:05.130
We can deal with it.
Doesn't change a thing.

53:05.290 --> 53:07.170
<i>MAN... sections
of Philadelphia and New York City.</i>

53:07.340 --> 53:09.340
You wanna get rid of it?

53:09.970 --> 53:10.970
Huh?

53:11.130 --> 53:13.760
Do you want to abort it?

53:14.800 --> 53:17.850
It's not too late. And I know how.

53:19.720 --> 53:23.100
<i>In other reports
now coming into our department...</i>

53:26.270 --> 53:28.570
<i>- Foreign sources...
- Let's get some sleep.</i>

53:28.730 --> 53:30.650
<i>...power crises throughout Europe...</i>

53:30.820 --> 53:35.240
<i>...and parts of Asia, where a state
of martial law will take effect...</i>

